# TaskFlow Supabase Configuration

Copy this to `.env.local` to enable team-sync mode with real-time collaboration:

```env
# Database Mode: 'local' (localStorage) or 'supabase' (cloud)
VITE_DATABASE_MODE=supabase

# Supabase Configuration
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key-here

# User ID for tracking changes (optional)
VITE_USER_ID=user-uuid-here

# Webhooks
VITE_WEBHOOK_URL=https://hooks.zapier.com/your-webhook-url
```

## Supabase Setup Instructions

### 1. Create a Supabase Project
- Go to [supabase.com](https://supabase.com)
- Click "New Project"
- Fill in project details and create

### 2. Create Database Tables

In the Supabase SQL editor, run:

```sql
-- Projects table
CREATE TABLE taskflow (
  id BIGINT PRIMARY KEY,
  title TEXT NOT NULL,
  client TEXT NOT NULL,
  stage_id BIGINT NOT NULL,
  priority TEXT DEFAULT 'Med',
  last_update TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW(),
  subtasks JSONB DEFAULT '[]',
  created_by TEXT,
  synced_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW(),
  updated_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
);

-- Enable real-time
ALTER PUBLICATION supabase_realtime ADD TABLE taskflow;
```

### 3. Enable RLS (Row Level Security)
```sql
ALTER TABLE taskflow ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;

-- Allow all authenticated users to read/write
CREATE POLICY "Enable read for authenticated users"
  ON taskflow FOR SELECT
  USING (true);

CREATE POLICY "Enable write for authenticated users"
  ON taskflow FOR INSERT
  WITH CHECK (true);

CREATE POLICY "Enable update for authenticated users"
  ON taskflow FOR UPDATE
  USING (true);
```

### 4. Copy Credentials

From Supabase dashboard:
- Go to Settings > API
- Copy your `URL` and `anon` key
- Paste into `.env.local`

### 5. Switch to Team Mode

Change your code to use the team-enabled store:

```javascript
// OLD: Single-user mode
import { useTaskFlow } from './store/useTaskFlow';

// NEW: Team-sync mode
import { useTaskFlow } from './lib/useTaskFlowTeam';
```

## Features

✓ Real-time updates across all team members
✓ Instant project status changes
✓ Conflict resolution (remote wins)
✓ Sync status indicator
✓ Fallback to localStorage if Supabase is down
✓ Backward compatible with existing data
